  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The HDA Intel sound card fails after suspend to RAM because codec communication flags are not properly reset during reinitialization. After the first timeout/resume cycle, the chip->polling_mode flag is set to 1 (line 912) and remains set through subsequent suspend/resume cycles, causing the driver to remain in polling mode instead of interrupt mode. Additionally, if chip->single_cmd is set to 1 as a fallback (line 951), the CORB/RIRB buffers are not reinitialized on resume (line 1222-1223 condition skips reinitialization when single_cmd is 1). The azx_init_chip function (line 1209-1230) needs to reset polling_mode to 0 when full_reset is 1, and potentially also handle single_cmd flag reset to ensure clean chip state after resume. The flags persist across suspend/resume cycles because azx_stop_chip() doesn't reset them and azx_init_chip() doesn't reset them either, leaving the hardware in an inconsistent state with stale mode flags that prevent proper codec communication."
}

